This paper proposes a deep learning framework for face recognition using multimodal information. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and stacked auto-encoders (SAEs), which are popular deep learning techniques used in image processing and feature extraction. This further supports the likelihood of the paper belonging to the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of limited training data and achieving high recognition rates, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of multimodal data and deep learning techniques also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a small ensemble system, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques and achieving high recognition rates suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
